- if any_sites?
  .col-md-3= render 'side'
%div{class: any_sites? ? 'col-md-9' : ''}
  .welcome
    %h2
      Hey there, I'm 
      = logo_big
      %span.hermes-title Hermes
    %h4 Below I'll give you just a few simple hints to set me up for your website
  .explain
    %ul.rules
      %li 
        Add the following code to your pages, inside your JavaScript/CoffeeScript. Preferably inside the <a href="http://api.jquery.com/ready/" target="_blank">domready</a> and <b>after</b> your app initialization.
        .embed-element
          %pre#embed_dynamic
            (function(d,l,s){s=d.createElement('script'),l=d.scripts[0];s.src='#{hermes_embed_url}';l.parentNode.insertBefore(s,l)}(document));
          %button.btn.btn-default.copy-element.btn-xs{:'data-clipboard-target' => "embed_dynamic"}
            copy

        <b>or</b> insert it statically just before the ending
        %code &lt;/body&gt;
        tag and <b>after</b> your page scripts:
        .embed-element
          %pre#embed_static
            &lt;script src="#{hermes_embed_url}"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
          %button.btn.btn-default.copy-element.btn-xs{:'data-clipboard-target' => "embed_static"}
            copy
      %li
        = link_to '#new-site-modal', class: 'btn btn-primary btn-lg', :'data-toggle' => 'modal' do
          Add new site
      %li
        %p
          Boom! Once you added a site, you can add
        %ul
          %li <b>Tips</b>: they will be shown to your visitors until they dismiss them. They can be bound to particular elements or they can be shown as broadcasts.
          %li <b>Tutorials</b>: collections of tips/broadcasts that will be shown to the visitors sequentially.
      %li
        Happy delivery, by Hermes! :)